title: AMOYAN FIGHTING COMPANY CONFIRMS LAUNCH OF INVICTUS FIGHT LEAGUE (IFL) SEASON 1
subtitle: The rebranded Invictus Fighting Championship (IFC) is all set to return as Invictus Fighting League (IFL) this November.
blurb: The ultimate female-only fighting extravaganza returns in an all-new flavour in the form of Invictus Fighting League (IFL). IFL's Season 1 will soon be launched in the first week of  November.
content:
Amoyan Fighting Company (AFC) today confirmed that Invictus Fight League (IFL) Season 1 will commence in the first week of November 2025, marking a new era in professional female combat sports.

The IFL succeeds the ten-season legacy of the Invictus Fighting Championship (IFC) and introduces a modern, data-driven competition format across three divisions, integrating updated global rankings, athlete analytics, and fan-interactive digital features through the new Amoyan FC portal.



“The IFL represents evolution — a league built on fairness, transparency, and performance,” said Rushabh Shah, CEO of AFC. “Every fighter enters with a clean slate but a rich history, and the global audience will witness the best iteration of women’s MMA yet.”


Season 1 will feature 38 fighters across Division 1, 2 and 3, competing in round-robin formats before promotion and relegation reshuffle the rankings for Season 2.


Broadcast:

  • India & South Asia: Jio Cinema / Star Sports Network
  • UK & Europe: DAZN Sports
  • USA & Australia: ESPN International
  • Russia & CIS: Okko Sports

AFC confirmed that all historical data from IFC, Champions Cup, and Invicta Cup have been migrated to the new digital platform, ensuring accurate legacy statistics and live analytics during IFL events.

The official fight calendar, venue list, and promotional visuals will be released next week.
